MOTORISTS and taxi owners can look forward to more money in their pockets with the price of petrol set to drop in July. The department of energy is likely to implement a retail petrol price drop of 69 cents per litre on 5 July, while the wholesale price of diesel could fall by 62 cents per litre, the Automobile Association announced. The AA said kasi and rural citizens who depend on paraffin for lighting, cooking and especially heating in the winter months would also get relief with the drop in prices. The AA said the rand remained firm this month, while the international oil and petroleum prices continued to drop. &ldquo;This adds up to a pleasing drop in the fuel price which will be a patch of good news for many in the current economic conditions,&rdquo; said the AA.